title: Presidential hopeful Hillary Rodham Clinton to guest on Colbert's 'Late Show' on Tuesday
text:
The Canadian Press - ONLINE EDITION Presidential hopeful Hillary Rodham Clinton to guest on Colbert's 'Late Show' on Tuesday By: The Associated Press Enlarge Image 
Democratic presidential candidate Hillary Rodham Clinton speaks during the Iowa Democratic Party's Jefferson-Jackson fundraising dinner, Saturday, Oct. 24, 2015, in Des Moines, Iowa. (AP Photo/Charlie Neibergall) 
NEW YORK, N.Y. - Hillary Rodham Clinton will pay a visit to "The Late Show With Stephen Colbert" on Tuesday. 
The Democratic presidential hopeful will be joined by other scheduled guests chief-TV-personality Anthony Bourdain and "Portlandia" star Carrie Brownstein, CBS said. 
Clinton follows past "Late Show" guests from the campaign trail including Jeb Bush, Bernie Sanders and Donald Trump.
